     </property>
     <property name="html">
      <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Ubuntu'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;This tool intends to give the user, useful information which can assist with systems troubleshooting. It is not a replacement for application support, or a service representative. . .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;The operations it offers are mainly read only, and diagnostic. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;write help stuff later.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
     </property>
    </widget>
   </widget>
   <widget class="QWidget" name="tab_2">
    <attribute name="title">
     <string>About</string>
    </attribute>
    <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit">
     <property name="geometry">
      <rect>
       <x>0</x>
       <y>10</y>
       <width>661</width>
       <height>731</height>
      </rect>
     </property>
     <property name="html">
      <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Ubuntu'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;What this Program Does:&lt;br /&gt;It reads registers on your PLC, and gives your some diagnostic information. We test both the PLC, and the Program Code, to verify current state, operability, investigate current errors, change the time, gather information, and or assist in diagnostics. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Why are there some many Errors? IDEC calls everyhing errors in the documentation.  Might most of these be better classified as warningings, alerts, or informational? Sure, but someone else can do the lexical analysis.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is not a WindLDR Clone, it is free software, its relivence outside specific, supported Heat Pump systems may be limited. You are free to use this software for educational purposes, without any waranty implied.  &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Version 0.0.0 Nyle PLC Systems Debugger&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;R&amp;amp;D and Controls testing. Not a commerial product.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Requires a Mini Usb cable. Tested on  MS Windows and Linux&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:16pt; font-weight:600;&quot;&gt;Created on 3/14/2026&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
     </property>
    </widget>
   </widget>
  </widget>
 </widget>
